{{redirect|BHAG|the city in Pakistan|Bhag}} {{Refimprove|date=June 2011}}
A '''Big Hairy Audacious Goal''' ('''BHAG''' - pronounced BEE-hag) is a [[strategic planning|strategic]] [[business statement]] similar to a [[vision statement]] which is created{{by whom?|date=October 2018}} to focus an [[organization]] on a single medium- to long-term organization-wide goal which is audacious, likely to be externally questionable, but not internally regarded as impossible.
[[James C. Collins|James Collins]] and [[Jerry Porras]] coined the term "Big Hairy Audacious Goal" in their 1994 book ''[[Built to Last: Successful Habits of Visionary Companies]]''.<ref>{{cite book|last1= Collins |first1= Jim |author1-link= James C. Collins |last2= Porras |first2= Jerry I. |author2-link= Jerry Porras |lastauthoramp= yes |title= Built To Last: Successful Habits of Visionary Companies |year= 1994 |publisher= HarperBusiness |isbn= 0-060-56610-8 |page= 113 }}</ref> A BHAG encourages organisations to define [[visionary (disambiguation) | visionary]] goals that are more strategic and emotionally compelling.{{cn|date=October 2018}} Many{{quantify|date=October 2018}} organisations set goals that describe what they hope to accomplish over the coming days, months or years. These goals help align employees to work together more effectively.{{cn|date=October 2018}} Often these goals are very tactical, such as "achieve 10% revenue growth in the next 3 months". In contrast, Collins and Porras define a BHAG as "an audacious 10-to-30-year goal to progress towards an envisioned future".<ref> {{cite journal |last1= Collins |first1= Jim |last2= Porras |first2= Jerry I. |lastauthoramp= yes |title= Building Your Company's Vision |date= September 1996 |journal= [[Harvard Business Review]] |volume= 74 |issue= 5 |pages= 65–77 |url= https://hbr.org/1996/09/building-your-companys-vision |subscription= yes }} </ref> The authors claim that a [[company]] may have more than one BHAG; there may be one over-reaching BHAG and other shorter-term BHAGs.
{{quote|text= "A true BHAG is clear and compelling, serves as unifying focal point of effort, and acts as a clear catalyst for [[team spirit]]. It has a clear finish line, so the organization can know when it has achieved the goal; people like to shoot for finish lines."|sign= Collins and Porras|source= [[Built to Last: Successful Habits of Visionary Companies]]}}
Mahoney and McCue sound a cautionary note when assessing BHAGs, seeing them as "[w]orthwhile when relevant to the business; inspiring to employees but disappointing when dropped in a few years in favor of other goals".<ref> {{cite web |url= https://wc.wustl.edu/files/wc/imce/insights_business_strategy.pdf |title= Insights From Business Strategy and Management 'Big Ideas' of the Past Three Decades: Are They Fads or Enablers? |last= Mahoney |first= Richard J. |last2= McCue |first2= Joseph A. |author-link2= |date= January 1999 |website= Washington University in St. Louis |series= The CEO Series |publisher= Center for the Study of American Business |agency= Center for the Study of American Business |location= St. Louis |page=16 |access-date= 2018-10-18 |quote= Worthwhile when relevant to the business; inspiring to employees but disappointing when dropped in a few years in favor of other goals. }} </ref>
==Notable examples== * [[John F. Kennedy|JFK's Moon Challenge]]: This nation should commit itself to achieving the goal, before this decade is out, of landing a man on the moon and returning him safely to the earth.<ref>[http://www.jfklibrary.org/Asset-Viewer/xzw1gaeeTES6khED14P1Iw.aspx Address Before a Joint Session of Congress, 25 May 1961]</ref> * [[Microsoft]]: A computer on every desk and in every home.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2015/06/microsoft-has-a-new-mission-statement-and-its-basically-the-same-as-its-old-one/|title=Microsoft has a new mission statement, and it’s basically the same as its old one|last=Bright|first=Peter|date=June 25, 2015|work=[[Ars Technica]]|accessdate=June 17, 2017|quote=Both are a far cry from the Bill Gates era. 'A computer on every desk and in every home' was clearer in intent and actually ''measurable''; it was a mission statement that allowed Microsoft to more or less say 'Mission accomplished.'}}</ref> * [[AIESEC]]: Engage and develop every young person in the world.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.aies.ec/ai-resources/2016/7/20/everything-2020|title=EVERYTHING 2020|work=AIESEC HUB|access-date=2017-11-24|language=en-US}}</ref> * [[SpaceX]]: Enable human exploration and settlement of Mars.<ref>{{cite news |title=Elon Musk: I'll Put a Man on Mars in 10 Years |url=http://www.marketwatch.com/video/asset/elon-musk-ill-put-a-man-on-mars-in-10-years-2011-04-22/CCF1FC62-BB0D-4561-938C-DF0DEFAD15BA#!CCF1FC62-BB0D-4561-938C-DF0DEFAD15BA |newspaper=Market Watch |date=2011-04-22 |publisher=The Wall Street Journal |location=New York |accessdate=2011-12-01 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63bvaGo3E?url=http://www.marketwatch.com/video/asset/elon-musk-ill-put-a-man-on-mars-in-10-years-2011-04-22/CCF1FC62-BB0D-4561-938C-DF0DEFAD15BA |deadurl=no |archivedate=2011-12-01 |df= }}</ref> * [[Blackpool FC]]: Reach English [[Premier League]].<ref>English Premier League, 05-22-2010, [http://englishpremierleague.com.my/2010/05/27/blackpool-football-club-2007/ English Premier League] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120426052405/http://englishpremierleague.com.my/2010/05/27/blackpool-football-club-2007/ |date=2012-04-26 }}, accessed on 12-15-2011.</ref> * [[Google]]: Organize the world's information and make it universally accessible and useful.<ref>[http://www.google.com/intl/en/corporate/index.html ''Company Overview'', ''Google.com'']</ref> * [[Hong Kong Broadband Network]]: Be the largest IP provider in Hong Kong by 2016.<ref>[http://media.telecoms.com/video_page/index.php?type=1&file=BBWF/William-Yeung.mp4 FTTH Deployment in Hong Kong: Successful Story of a Forerunner]</ref> * [[SolarAid]]: To eradicate the kerosene lamp from Africa by 2020<ref>{{cite web |title=Big, Hairy and Audacious. Not our CEO...our BHAG! |website=SolarAid |date=29 June 2012 |url=http://www.solar-aid.org/big-hairy-and-audacious/ |archive-date=13 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160813143723/http://solar-aid.org/big-hairy-and-audacious/ }}</ref> * [[Gift of Life Marrow Registry]]: To cure blood cancer through marrow donation by ensuring a match for every patient in need, whenever they need one.<ref>[http://www.giftoflife.org ''Gift of Life Marrow Registry'']</ref> * [[Volvo]]: By 2020 no one should be killed or seriously injured in a new Volvo .<ref>[http://www.volvocars.com/intl/about/vision-2020 ''Volvo website'']</ref> * [[Feeding Everyone No Matter What]]: Prevent starvation even if the sun is blocked by [[Nuclear Winter]], [[Volcanic winter]] or [[Impact Winter]].<ref>[http://www.allfed.info ''Alliance to Feed the Earth in Disasters website'']</ref> *[http://practicalacademics.com/ Practical Academics]. To empower and support people to spend 3-5 hours / week in lifelong learning.
