'''Gérard Dubois''' is a [[Swiss]] born chef and businessman, focusing on patisseries, boulangeries and confiseries.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}  In 1991, Dubois opened the first [[La Rose Noire]] patisserie in [[Pacific Place (Hong Kong)|Pacific Place]], Admiralty, [[Hong Kong]].{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}

La Rose Noire has produced several publications — in 2003, 2006 and 2011. The latest edition ''Crafted Passion'' (2011) was awarded 'Best Dessert Book in the World,' from the [[Gourmand World Cookbook Awards|Gourmand Awards]] in Paris.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gourmand Awards Winners 2011|url=http://www.cookbookfair.com/index.php/gourmand-awards/winners/winners/cookbooks|publisher=Cookbookfair.com|accessdate=2012-09-24|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114133124/http://www.cookbookfair.com/index.php/gourmand-awards/winners/winners/cookbooks|archivedate=2012-11-14|df=}}</ref> He has also been a regular panel judge at renowned international competitions.

His latest venture [[Passion by Gerard Dubois]] is a patisserie, boulangerie and confiserie in [[Wan Chai]], [[Hong Kong]].{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}

